\s4 Full kingdom
\r (1 Sam. 31:1-13)
\p
\v 1 \add âNow\add* the Philistines foughtÂŠ192200 against YisraelÂŠ192201 and the IsraeliÂŠ192205 men fled \add âaway\add* from the Philistines, and \add âmany were killed\add* on Mt. GilboaÂŠ192211.
\v 2 ThenÂŠ192213 the PhilistinesÂŠ192214 pursuedÂŠ192213 after ShaulÂŠ192216 and after his sons, and \add *they\add* \add âkilledÂŠ192219\add* \add his\add* sons Yonatan, Avinadav, and Malki-ShuaÂŠ192231.
\v 3 The battleÂŠ192236 against ShaulÂŠ192239 was very fierce, \add âbut thenÂŠ192235\add* the archers spotted him andÂŠ192235 woundedÂŠ192243 him.
\v 4 ThenÂŠ192248 Shaul said to his equipment carrier, âDraw your sword and pierce me with it, so those uncircumcisedÂŠ192262 \add Philistines\add* \add ^can't come here\add* and torture me.â ButÂŠ192248 his equipment carrier was very scared and wasn't willingÂŠ192268 to do it, so Shaul took \add &his\add* sword and fell onto it.
\v 5 ThenÂŠ192283 his equipment carrier, seeing that \add King\add* ShaulÂŠ192289 had died, he himself fell on \add &his\add* sword andÂŠ192283 died.
\v 6 \add âSo\add* ShaulÂŠ192301 and his threeÂŠ192302 sonsÂŠ192303 died, \add âthus ending his family's rule\add*.
\v 7 \add âWhenÂŠ192314 all the IsraelisÂŠ192313 living\add* in the valleyÂŠ192317 sawÂŠ192310 that \add @the army\add* had fled, and that ShaulÂŠ192323 and his sonsÂŠ192324 were dead, they abandonedÂŠ192325 theirÂŠ192326 citiesÂŠ192326 and fled. ThenÂŠ192310 the PhilistinesÂŠ192329 cameÂŠ192328, and they livedÂŠ192330 in them \add instead\add*.
\p
\v 8 The next dayÂŠ192335 \add âwhen\add* the PhilistinesÂŠ192337 cameÂŠ192336 to stripÂŠ192338 the deadÂŠ192341, theyÂŠ192336 foundÂŠ192342 \add âthe bodies of\add* ShaulÂŠ192345 and his sonsÂŠ192348 on Mt. GilboaÂŠ192351.
\v 9 They strippedÂŠ192353 himÂŠ192353 and carried away his head and his armourÂŠ192360. ThenÂŠ192353 they sentÂŠ192361 \add messengers\add* all aroundÂŠ192366 the Philistine \add âregions\add* to take the newsÂŠ192367 to theirÂŠ192370 idolsÂŠ192370 and the peopleÂŠ192373.
\v 10 They put his armourÂŠ192378 in the \add âtemple\add* of their godsÂŠ192380, andÂŠ192375 theyÂŠ192384 hung his head in \add their god\add* Dagon'sÂŠ192386 \add âtemple\add*.
\v 11 \add âWhen\add* everyone who lived \add back\add* in Yavesh in the GileadÂŠ192392 region heardÂŠ192389 about everything that the PhilistinesÂŠ192399 had done to ShaulÂŠ192400,
\v 12 all the strong men \add âtookÂŠ192407 action\add* and \add âretrieved\add* the corpsesÂŠ192410 of ShaulÂŠ192411 and his sonsÂŠ192414, and broughtÂŠ192415 them \add back\add* to Yavesh. ThenÂŠ192402 they buriedÂŠ192417 \add âthem\add* underÂŠ192421 the large tree in Yavesh, and they fastedÂŠ192424 sevenÂŠ192425 daysÂŠ192426.
\v 13 \add âSoÂŠ192428\add* ShaulÂŠ192429 diedÂŠ192428 because of his \add âdisobedience\add*âwhen he was unfaithfulÂŠ192430 to Yahweh \add âby not following Yahweh's instructions\add*, andÂŠ192428 also \add âbecause he consultedÂŠ192444 mediumÂŠ192445\add* \add for guidance\add*\x + \xo 10:13: a \xt 1Sam 13:8-14; 15:1-24; \xo b \xt Lev 19:31; 20:6; 1Sam 28:7-8.\x*
\v 14 \add âinstead of requesting Yahweh'sÂŠ192451 advice\add*. \add âSoÂŠ192448\add* \add @Yahweh\add* killed himÂŠ192452 andÂŠ192448 handed the kingdom over to Yishay'sÂŠ192460 son DavidÂŠ192457.
\c 11
\s1 David becomes king
\rem /s1 David Becomes King Over Israel; David Becomes King of All Israel; David Becomes King of Israel and Judah; David Anointed King of All Israel
\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Sam. 5:1-10)
\p
\v 1 Then all YisraelÂŠ192466 assembled around DavidÂŠ192469 at Hevron, saying, âLook, we're your fleshÂŠ192474 and bone \add relatives\add*.
\v 2 \add âIn the recent past\add*, even when ShaulÂŠ192485 was kingÂŠ192486, \em you\em* were the one who took Yisrael out and the one who broughtÂŠ192489 us back in. Plus your godÂŠ192495 YahwehÂŠ192494 told you, âYou yourself will shepherdÂŠ192498 my people, Yisrael, and you yourself will become leader of my Israeli people.â â
\v 3 \add âSoÂŠ192512\add* all the IsraeliÂŠ192515 eldersÂŠ192515 wentÂŠ192512 to the king at Hevron, andÂŠ192512 David made a solemn agreement with them at Hevron \add âin frontÂŠ192526\add* of Yahweh. ThenÂŠ192512 they anointedÂŠ192528 David as king over YisraelÂŠ192516 accordingÂŠ192536 to Yahweh's messageÂŠ192536 \add âthat was given through\add* \add the prophet\add* Shemuel \add (SamuelÂŠ192540)\add*.
\rem /s1 David Captures Jerusalem; David Conquers Jerusalem; Jerusalem Captured
\p
\v 4 Then DavidÂŠ192544 and all YisraelÂŠ192547 wentÂŠ192543 to YerushalemÂŠ192548 (\add Jerusalem, which was also known as\add* Yevus \add âbecause the Yevusites were living thereÂŠ192551\add*).\x + \xo 11:4: \xt Josh 15:63; Jdg 1:21.\x*
\v 5 The inhabitantsÂŠ192557 \add âinside\add* Yevus saidÂŠ192556 to David, âYou won'tÂŠ192560 \add âbe entering this place\add*.â ButÂŠ192556 David capturedÂŠ192563 \add what became known as\add* the TsiyyonÂŠ192568 \add (ZionÂŠ192568)\add* strongholdÂŠ192567, that is, the cityÂŠ192570 of David.
\v 6 \add *He\add* had saidÂŠ192573, âWhoever strikes down the Yevusites first will becomeÂŠ192580 \add âmy army commanderÂŠ192581\add*.â Tseruyah's son Yoav went up \add over the wall\add* first, andÂŠ192573 he became head \add of the army\add*.
\v 7 David \add started\add* living in that strongholdÂŠ192594, so thenÂŠ192592 they calledÂŠ192598 it the cityÂŠ192601 of David.
\v 8 He builtÂŠ192604 the city up all aroundÂŠ192606, from the terrace \add âto the surroundingÂŠ192612 walls\add*, andÂŠ192604 Yoav restoredÂŠ192614 the rest of the city.
\v 9 \add âSoÂŠ192620\add* DavidÂŠ192621 \add âbecame more powerfulÂŠ192623 because\add* army commander YahwehÂŠ192624 \add âhelped\add* him.
\s1 David's powerful warriors
\rem /s1 David's Famous Soldiers; David's Mighty Men; David's Mighty Men and Their Exploits; David's Mightiest Men
\s4 Full kingdom
\rem /r (2 Samuel 23.8-39)
\p
\v 10 TheÂŠ192647 following were the leaders of David'sÂŠ192633 powerful warriors who together with all YisraelÂŠ192641, strengthened his kingdomÂŠ192636 andÂŠ192629 established himÂŠ192642 as kingÂŠ192642, \add âjust as\add* YahwehÂŠ192644 had said.
\v 11 \add âSo\add* theseÂŠ192650 are David'sÂŠ192654 powerfulÂŠ192652 warriors: Yashaveam (a Hakmonite \add and\add* the leader of the thirty) once \add âused\add* his spearÂŠ192667 against three hundredÂŠ192672 men in a single battle and killed them all.
\v 12 Next was EleazarÂŠ192678 (an AhohiteÂŠ192682, son of DodoÂŠ192681) who was one of the \add top\add* threeÂŠ192684 powerfulÂŠ192685 warriors.
\v 13 He was with DavidÂŠ192692 at Pas-Dammim \add âwhen\add* the Philistines had assembled thereÂŠ192698 for battleÂŠ192700 \add ânear\add* a part of the countrysideÂŠ192703 \add âwhere barleyÂŠ192705 was growing\add*. \add âAt first, the Israelis\add* fled from the Philistines,
\v 14 \add âbut thenÂŠ192711\add* they tookÂŠ192711 their standÂŠ192711 in the middleÂŠ192712 of the \add âbarley\add* andÂŠ192711 \add âproceeded to defeat\add* the PhilistinesÂŠ192719 \add âas\add* YahwehÂŠ192721 savedÂŠ192720 them through a stunning victoryÂŠ192722.
\p
\v 15 ThenÂŠ192725 threeÂŠ192726 of that top thirtyÂŠ192729 wentÂŠ192725 down to DavidÂŠ192736, near the rockÂŠ192733 at Adullam'sÂŠ192740 cave. \add âMeanwhile,\add* PhilistinesÂŠ192742 had encampedÂŠ192743 in the RefaimÂŠ192745 Valley.
\v 16 David was in that strongholdÂŠ192749 thenÂŠ192747, andÂŠ192750 the Philistine garrisonÂŠ192750 was in Beyt-Lehem
\v 17 and DavidÂŠ192758 \add âwas thirsty and asked\add*, âWho'll get me waterÂŠ192762 to drinkÂŠ192761 from the well by the Beyt-Lehem gateÂŠ192768?â
\v 18 \add âSoÂŠ192770 those\add* threeÂŠ192771 brokeÂŠ192770 through the Philistine camp, and they drew waterÂŠ192776 from the well at the Beyt-Lehem gateÂŠ192782, and they broughtÂŠ192784 it back to David. \add âButÂŠ192770\add* David wasn't willingÂŠ192790 to drinkÂŠ192792 it, and he pouredÂŠ192793 it out \add on the ground as an offering\add* to YahwehÂŠ192795.
\v 19 âFar be it from me beforeÂŠ192800 my godÂŠ192800 \add âto drink this water\add*,â he said. âCould I drink the bloodÂŠ192803 of these menÂŠ192804 \add âwho risked\add* their lives to bring it?â \add âSoÂŠ192797\add* he wasn't \add âprepared\add* to drink it. Those were \add some of the things\add* that those threeÂŠ192816 powerful warriors did.
\rem /s1 David's Thirty Mighty Men
\p
\v 20 Yoav's brotherÂŠ192820 Abshai, was the head of a group of three. He had killed three hundredÂŠ192836 with is spearÂŠ192832 and had a reputation among the three.\f + \fr 11:20 \ft This seems unexpectedly similar to verse 11 and might possibly indicate some confusion in the early records.\f*
\v 21 He was honouredÂŠ192848 more than the other two and became the leader of that \add ?second\add* group of three, \add âbut\add* didn'tÂŠ192855 enter the \add ?first\add* Three.
\p
\v 22 Yehoyada's son BenayahÂŠ192860 from Kavtse'el was a powerful warriorÂŠ192879 who did amazing things. He struckÂŠ192876 down Ariel's twoÂŠ192878 \add sons\add* from MoabÂŠ192880. \add âAnother time,\add* he climbed down into a pit on a snowyÂŠ192890 dayÂŠ192889 and killedÂŠ192883 the lionÂŠ192886 \add âthat was trapped\add* in the pit.
\v 23 He \add also\add* \add âkilled\add* a \add âhuge\add* Egyptian manâwell over 2m tall. The Egyptian \add âwas carrying\add* a spear like a weaver'sÂŠ192908 beam, but \add @Benayah\add* went down to \add take him on\add* with a staff. He forced the spear from the Egyptian's \add âgrasp\add*, andÂŠ192892 thenÂŠ192892 killed him with \add *it\add*.
\v 24 \add So\add* that was what BenayahÂŠ192923 (Yehoyada's son) did \add âthat gave him a reputation\add* among the threeÂŠ192930 powerfulÂŠ192931 warriors.
\v 25 \add Actually,\add* he was honouredÂŠ192937 more than the Thirty, \add âyet\add* he didn'tÂŠ192942 \add âmake it to\add* the \add first\add* Three, \add âbut\add* DavidÂŠ192946 \add âappointed\add* him over his bodyguardsÂŠ192949.
\p
\v 26 These are the names of the powerful warriors: Asahel (Yoav's brotherÂŠ192957), ElhananÂŠ192959 (Dodo'sÂŠ192962 son from Beyt-Lehem),
\v 27 ShammotÂŠ192967 (from Haror), Helets (from Pelon),
\v 28 IraÂŠ192973 (Ikkesh'sÂŠ192976 son from TekoaÂŠ192977), AviezerÂŠ192978 (from AnatotÂŠ192979),
\v 29 Sibbekai (from Hushah), IlaiÂŠ192984 (from Ahoh),
\v 30 MaharaiÂŠ192988 (from Netofah), HeledÂŠ192990 (Baanah'sÂŠ192993 son from Netofah),
\v 31 ItaiÂŠ192997 (Rivai's son from Giveah which belonged to Benyamin'sÂŠ193003 descendantsÂŠ193002), BenayahÂŠ193005 (from Piraton),
\v 32 Hurai (from the valleys near Mt. GaashÂŠ193010), Aviel (from Aravah),
\v 33 AzmavetÂŠ193016 (from Baharum), Elyahba (from Shaalvon),
\v 34 Hashem'sÂŠ193023 sonsÂŠ193022 (from Gizon), Yonatan (Shagee'sÂŠ193028 son from Harar),
\v 35 AhiamÂŠ193032 (Sakar'sÂŠ193035 son from HararÂŠ193036), ElifalÂŠ193037 (Ur'sÂŠ193040 son),
\v 36 HeferÂŠ193043 (from Mekerat), Ahiyyah (from Pelon),
\v 37 HezroÂŠ193049 (from KarmelÂŠ193050), NaaraiÂŠ193051 (Ezbai'sÂŠ193054 son),
\v 38 YoelÂŠ193057 (Natan'sÂŠ193059 brotherÂŠ193058), MivharÂŠ193060 (Hagri'sÂŠ193063 son),
\v 39 TselekÂŠ193066 (the AmmoniteÂŠ193067), NaharaiÂŠ193068 (from BeerotÂŠ193069, armourÂŠ193071 bearerÂŠ193070 for Tseruyah's son Yoav),
\v 40 IraÂŠ193078 (the Yitrite), Garev (the Yitrite),
