\r (2 Sam. 12:26-31)
\p
\v 1 \add âThen in the spring when kingsÂŠ196490 often march out to war\add*, Yoav led the army out for war and he devastated the land of the Ammonites. Then he reached \add the capital,\add* Rabbah, and he besieged it while DavidÂŠ196510 stayed in YerushalemÂŠ196512. Yoav \add âdefeated\add* Rabbah and \add âdemolished the city\add*.\x + \xo 20:1: \xt 2Sam 11:1.\x*
\v 2 ThenÂŠ196520 DavidÂŠ196521 took theirÂŠ196526 king's crown off his headâit was goldÂŠ196534 with a valuable gemstone set in out, andÂŠ196520 \add âweighedÂŠ196531 thirty kilograms\add*. HeÂŠ196542 put \add @the crown\add* on his own head, plus he took a very large amount of plunder out of the cityÂŠ196544.
\v 3 ThenÂŠ196549 they took all the people out of the city and \add âforced them to work\add* with saws and iron picksÂŠ196558, and axesÂŠ196560. DavidÂŠ196563 did thatÂŠ196552 for the people of all the Ammonite citiesÂŠ196565, thenÂŠ196549 he returnedÂŠ196569 to YerushalemÂŠ196574 with his army.
