\r (2 Sam. 21:15-22)
\p
\v 4 \add âSome time later,\add* war brokeÂŠ196581 out with the PhilistinesÂŠ196586 at GezerÂŠ196583, then Sibbekai the HushatiteÂŠ196590 struckÂŠ196588 down SippaiÂŠ196593, from the descendantsÂŠ196594 of the Refaim, and they were subduedÂŠ196596.
\p
\v 5 ThenÂŠ196598 there was another battleÂŠ196601 with the PhilistinesÂŠ196604, andÂŠ196598 Yair'sÂŠ196609 son ElhananÂŠ196606 \add âkilledÂŠ196605\add* LahmiÂŠ196613 the brotherÂŠ196614 of Goliyat \add (GoliathÂŠ196615)\add*\x + \xo 20:5: \xt 1Sam 17:4-7.\x* the GittiteÂŠ196616 \add (i.e., from Gat)\add*, even though his spearÂŠ196618 shaft was \add as thick\add* as the beam of a weaver'sÂŠ196620 \add loom\add*.
\v 6 There was also war at GatÂŠ196626 where there was a \add âvery tall manÂŠ196629 with six fingersÂŠ196631 on each hand andÂŠ196622 six toes on each foot who was also a descendant\add* of Rafa.
\v 7 \add âWhen\add* he insulted YisraelÂŠ196646, Shimea'sÂŠ196651 son Yonatan killedÂŠ196647 him. (Shimea was one of David'sÂŠ196653 \add older\add* brothersÂŠ196652.)
\p
\v 8 Those were the descendants of Rafa from GatÂŠ196658 who were killed by DavidÂŠ196662 and he men.
\c 21
\s1 David orders a census
