\s4 Full kingdom
\r (2 Sam. 24:1-25)
\s2 Yoav doesn't want to do the census
\p
\v 1 Then a trouble-maker went against Yisrael \add âby\add* encouraging DavidÂŠ196676 \add âto take a census of\add* Yisrael,
\v 2 \add âSoÂŠ196682\add* DavidÂŠ196683 \add âordered\add* Yoav and \add âthe other officials\add*, âGo \add and\add* countÂŠ196692 YisraelÂŠ196695 from Be'er-Sheva \add in the south\add* and as far \add north\add* as DanÂŠ196700, \add âthenÂŠ196682 come and tell me so that I'll knowÂŠ196703 how many warriors I have\add*.â
\p
\v 3 âMy master, the kingÂŠ196721, may YahwehÂŠ196720 \add âmultiply his peopleÂŠ196714 one hundredÂŠ196717 timesÂŠ196718 over\add*. Aren't they all \add *your\add* servantsÂŠ196724?â Yoav \add diplomatically\add* \add âqueried\add*, â\add SoÂŠ196708\add* why does my master \add âwant to do\add* this? Why should \add âhe bring judgement on\add* YisraelÂŠ196732?â
\v 4 \add âButÂŠ196734 the kingÂŠ196736 insisted, so Yoav was forced to go andÂŠ196734 survey the entireÂŠ196744 country\add*. ThenÂŠ196734 he returned to YerushalemÂŠ196748
\v 5 and \add âreported the numbersÂŠ196754\add* to DavidÂŠ196760. YisraelÂŠ196764 had 1.1 million sword-wielding men, and Yehudah had 470 thousandÂŠ196766.
\v 6 \add âHowever,\add* \add @Yoav\add* had \add intentionally\add* not counted \add the tribes of\add* Levi andÂŠ196782 BenyaminÂŠ196782, because \add *he\add* was horrified by the king's command.
\s2 Punishment for the census
\rem /s1 Judgment for David's Sin
\p
\v 7 God \add âwas displeasedÂŠ196796 by what David had ordered, andÂŠ196796 he punished\add* YisraelÂŠ196806,
\v 8 and DavidÂŠ196810 saidÂŠ196809 to God, âI've \add âdisobeyed you badly by doing that\add*. Please \add âforgive yourÂŠ196829 servantÂŠ196829 for his disobedience\add*, because I've \add âbeen very stupid\add*.â
\p
\v 9 Then YahwehÂŠ196836 told David'sÂŠ196841 prophet GadÂŠ196839,
\v 10 âGo and tell DavidÂŠ196848 that YahwehÂŠ196852 saysÂŠ196851 this: \add âI'll give you threeÂŠ196853 optionsâchooseÂŠ196857 one of them and that's what I'll\add* do to you.â
\p
\v 11 \add âSoÂŠ196866\add* GadÂŠ196867 wentÂŠ196866 to DavidÂŠ196870 andÂŠ196871 told his, âYahwehÂŠ196876 saysÂŠ196875 that you must choose \add one of these punishments\add*:
\v 12 either three yearsÂŠ196884 of famineÂŠ196885, or three monthsÂŠ196889 of beingÂŠ196890 overcome by your enemies' \add âarmies\add*, or three daysÂŠ196901 of Yahweh's âswordâ of pestilenceÂŠ196904 in the land and the Yahweh's messengerÂŠ196906 \add âbringingÂŠ196917 destructionÂŠ196908\add* across all of Yisrael's territoryÂŠ196911. \add âSo now, tell me what answer I should take\add* back to the one who sent me?â
\p
\v 13 â\add Oh,\add* that's very distressingÂŠ196929,â DavidÂŠ196925 \add âreplied\add* to GadÂŠ196928, âbut please don'tÂŠ196947 let me fall into the handsÂŠ196944 of \add âmy enemies\add*. YahwehÂŠ196938 \add âis very merciful, so please let him be the one to punish me directly\add*.â
\p
\v 14 \add âSoÂŠ196951\add* YahwehÂŠ196952 \add âsent a disease\add* throughout YisraelÂŠ196954 andÂŠ196951 seventyÂŠ196957 thousandÂŠ196958 IsraeliÂŠ196956 men \add âdied\add*.
\v 15 ThenÂŠ196961 God sentÂŠ196961 a messenger to destroy YerushalemÂŠ196966, and \add âwhile the disease was still spreading\add* Yahweh \add âlooked down\add* and relented about the tragedy, and he told to the destroying messenger, âEnough! Now release your handÂŠ196981.â Now Yahweh's messenger \add happened to be\add* standingÂŠ196984 at the threshingÂŠ196987 floorÂŠ196987 of OrnanÂŠ196988 the Yevusite.
\p
\v 16 \add As\add* David \add âlooked up\add*, he sawÂŠ196997 Yahweh's messengerÂŠ197000 standingÂŠ197002 between the earthÂŠ197004 and the heavensÂŠ197006, holding his swordÂŠ197007 stretchedÂŠ197010 out over YerushalemÂŠ197013. Then David and the eldersÂŠ197016 who were \add all\add* dressed in sackclothÂŠ197018, fell \add âto their knees and bowed their facesÂŠ197021 to the ground\add*.
\v 17 ThenÂŠ197023 DavidÂŠ197024 \add âasked\add* GodÂŠ197046, âWasn't it me myself who said to countÂŠ197031 the people? It's me who \add âdisobeyed and clearly did what was wrongÂŠ197039\add*, but theseÂŠ197041 sheepÂŠ197042, what have they done? YahwehÂŠ197045 my godÂŠ197046, pleaseÂŠ197048 \add âdirect your punishment\add* against me and \add âmy extended family\add*, but \add âdon'tÂŠ197028 continue this\add* plagueÂŠ197055 on your people.â
\rem /s1 David's Altar and Sacrifice; David Builds an Altar
\p
\v 18 Then Yahweh's messengerÂŠ197058 told GadÂŠ197063 to tell DavidÂŠ197065 that \add *he\add* should \add âbuild\add* an altarÂŠ197071 to Yahweh at the threshingÂŠ197073 floorÂŠ197073 of OrnanÂŠ197074 the Yevusite.
\v 19 \add âSoÂŠ197077\add* DavidÂŠ197078 went up \add to that place when heÂŠ197083 heard\add* \add âGad'sÂŠ197081 messageÂŠ197079 that was delivered\add* in Yahweh'sÂŠ197085 nameÂŠ197084.
\v 20 \add âMeanwhile,\add* OrnanÂŠ197088 was threshingÂŠ197098 wheatÂŠ197099, and he turnedÂŠ197087 and sawÂŠ197089 \add Yahweh's\add* messengerÂŠ197092 and he and his fourÂŠ197093 sonsÂŠ197094 who were with him \add quickly\add* hid \add âbehind something\add*.
\v 21 \add âWhen David arrived there,\add* OrnanÂŠ197105 sawÂŠ197108 him and left the threshingÂŠ197115 floorÂŠ197115 and \add âknelt\add* in front of David and bowedÂŠ197116 his faceÂŠ197118 to the groundÂŠ197119.
\v 22 ThenÂŠ197121 DavidÂŠ197122 \add âasked\add* OrnanÂŠ197125, âGive me this placeÂŠ197129 with its threshingÂŠ197130 floorÂŠ197130, andÂŠ197121 I'll buildÂŠ197131 an altarÂŠ197134 to YahwehÂŠ197135 on it. \add âSell it to me\add* at the full priceÂŠ197136, so the plagueÂŠ197141 against the peopleÂŠ197143 will be stoppedÂŠ197140.â
\p
\v 23 âMy masterÂŠ197154 the kingÂŠ197155, takeÂŠ197150 \add âanything that you want\add*,â OrnanÂŠ197146 \add âreplied\add*. âListen, I'll donate the cattle for the burntÂŠ197161 offerings and the threshingÂŠ197162 sledgesÂŠ197162 for firewood, and the wheatÂŠ197164 for the offeringâall \add âat no charge\add*.â
\p
\v 24 âNo, I'll most definitely pay the full priceÂŠ197178,â King DavidÂŠ197171 \add ârespondedÂŠ197169\add*. âI couldn't offer a burntÂŠ197189 offering to YahwehÂŠ197187 \add âif it hadn't cost me anything\add*.â
\v 25 \add âSoÂŠ197192\add* DavidÂŠ197193 paid OrnanÂŠ197194 sixÂŠ197199 hundredÂŠ197200 goldÂŠ197197 pieces for \add &his\add* place,
\v 26 and he builtÂŠ197202 an altar to Yahweh thereÂŠ197203 and offered burnt offerings and peaceÂŠ197209 offerings on it. He calledÂŠ197210 to Yahweh, and \add @Yahweh\add* answeredÂŠ197214 him with fireÂŠ197215 from the heavensÂŠ197218 on that altar of the burnt offering.
\p
\v 27 Then YahwehÂŠ197225 spoke to \add &his\add* messengerÂŠ197226 who then returned his swordÂŠ197228 to his sheathÂŠ197231.
\s1 The location for the future temple
