\v 28 When DavidÂŠ197236 sawÂŠ197235 that YahwehÂŠ197240 had answeredÂŠ197239 him at (the Yevusite) Ornan'sÂŠ197242 threshingÂŠ197241 floorÂŠ197241, then he sacrificedÂŠ197244 thereÂŠ197245.
\v 29 \add âAt that timeÂŠ197256\add*, Yahweh's \add sacredÂŠ197247\add* tentÂŠ197247 that MoshehÂŠ197252 \add (MosesÂŠ197252)\add* had made in the wildernessÂŠ197253, andÂŠ197254 the altarÂŠ197254 for burntÂŠ197255 sacrifices, were \add âon a hill used for worship near\add* GibeonÂŠ197259 \add city\add*.
\v 30 DavidÂŠ197264 wasn't able to goÂŠ197265 there to \add âask God's direction\add* because he was terrifiedÂŠ197270 of Yahweh's messenger'sÂŠ197273 swordÂŠ197272.
\c 22
\p
\v 1 Then DavidÂŠ197278 saidÂŠ197277, âThis is \add now\add* the residence of YahwehÂŠ197282 God, and this is the altarÂŠ197286 for Yisrael's burntÂŠ197287 \add #offering\add*.â
\s1 The preparation of standing up of temple
\rem /s1 Preparations for the Temple; Preparation for the temple; Preparations for Building the Temple; David Prepares to Build the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 2 Then DavidÂŠ197292 saidÂŠ197291 to gather the foreigners who \add âlived\add* in IsraelÂŠ197299, and he assigned \add âthem the job of\add* hewing out cut stonesÂŠ197303 to buildÂŠ197305 the residenceÂŠ197296 for God.
\v 3 HeÂŠ197317 preparedÂŠ197316 a large quantity of iron for the door \add âhinges andÂŠ197309 fittings\add*, so much brass that it couldn't be weighedÂŠ197321,
\v 4 and innumerable cedar logs that the Tsidonians and the Tsorians \add (SidoniansÂŠ197329 and TyriansÂŠ197330)\add* broughtÂŠ197328 in for DavidÂŠ197334.
\v 5 David saidÂŠ197337, âMy son Shelomoh \add (SolomonÂŠ197339)\add* is young and tender, and the houseÂŠ197343 to be builtÂŠ197344 for YahwehÂŠ197345 must be \add âimpressive for the sake of his reputation\add* and for beauty in all the landsÂŠ197353 \add so\add* I'll prepare for it now.â \add âSo\add* David prepared a large amount before \add âhe died\add*.
\rem /s1 David's Charge to Solomon and the Leaders
\p
\v 6 ThenÂŠ197363 David calledÂŠ197363 for his son Shelomoh \add (SolomonÂŠ197364)\add*, andÂŠ197366 ordered himÂŠ197366 to buildÂŠ197367 a residence for Yisrael's godÂŠ197370 YahwehÂŠ197369.
\v 7 DavidÂŠ197375 told \add *him\add*, âMy son, I wanted to buildÂŠ197384 a temple to honour my godÂŠ197388 YahwehÂŠ197387,\x + \xo 22:7-10: \xt 2Sam 7:1-16; 1Ch 17:1-14.\x*
\v 8 \add âbut\add* YahwehÂŠ197394 \add âgave me this messageÂŠ197392\add*, âYou've fought a lot of battles andÂŠ197390 shed a large amount of blood, \add so\add* you won'tÂŠ197402 be the one who'll buildÂŠ197404 a residence \add âto honour me\add*âyou've shed too much blood on the ground \add âin myÂŠ197412 sightÂŠ197412\add*.â
\v 9 \add He told me,\add* âListen, you'll have a son who'll be a manÂŠ197421 of peace. I'll give him relief from all his enemiesÂŠ197427 from the surrounding regions. That's why he'll be called âShelomohâ \add (which sounds like âShalomââthe Hebrew word for peace)\add*, and I'll give peace and quietnessÂŠ197434 to YisraelÂŠ197438 during his lifetime.
\v 10 He'll be the one to buildÂŠ197443 a residence for me, and he himself will become my son, and I'll become his fatherÂŠ197454, and I'll establishÂŠ197455 the throneÂŠ197456 of his kingdomÂŠ197457 over YisraelÂŠ197460 forever.â
\p
\v 11 âNow, my son, may Yahweh be with you, and may you be successfulÂŠ197470 and buildÂŠ197471 a residence for Yahweh your godÂŠ197474, just as he said you would.
\v 12 \add âI also ask\add* Yahweh to give you insightÂŠ197484 and understandingÂŠ197485, and give you chargeÂŠ197486 over YisraelÂŠ197489 so that you can keep your godÂŠ197495 Yahweh's regulations.
\v 13 Then you'll succeedÂŠ197498, if you are careful to follow the instructions and the directions thatÂŠ197509 YahwehÂŠ197511 commandedÂŠ197510 MoshehÂŠ197514 \add (MosesÂŠ197514)\add* concerning YisraelÂŠ197517. Be strongÂŠ197518 and courageousÂŠ197519. Don't be afraidÂŠ197522 or discouraged.\x + \xo 22:13: \xt Josh 1:6-9.\x*
\p
\v 14 Now, see, \add ?âdespite many battles\add*, I've prepared the following for Yahweh's residence: three thousand tonnes of goldÂŠ197533 and thirty thousand tonnes of silverÂŠ197538, along with too much bronzeÂŠ197542 and iron to weighÂŠ197545, and timberÂŠ197549 and \add cut\add* stonesÂŠ197550. Plus you'll be able to add more.
\v 15 \add âYou'll have plenty of skilledÂŠ197565 workers including those who work with stoneÂŠ197561 andÂŠ197555 those who work with wood\add*.
\v 16 \add âThen there'sÂŠ197574 so many skilled with goldÂŠ197570 and silverÂŠ197571, and bronzeÂŠ197572 and iron. So get organised and get started\add*, and may YahwehÂŠ197579 be with youÂŠ197580.
\p
\v 17 ThenÂŠ197582 DavidÂŠ197583 orderedÂŠ197582 all the IsraeliÂŠ197586 officialsÂŠ197586 to assist his son Shelomoh, \add saying\add*,
\v 18 âIsn't Yahweh your godÂŠ197594 with you all, and hasn't he given peace to you all from all around, because he's \add âallowed me to take control of this region, and this area has been subduedÂŠ197606 with the help\add* of Yahweh and his peopleÂŠ197611.
\v 19 Now, \add âdedicate your mindÂŠ197615 and strength to request advice from your godÂŠ197619 Yahweh, then get organised and buildÂŠ197621 the sanctuaryÂŠ197624 of Yahweh God so you can bring the box containing Yahweh's agreement to the residence to be builtÂŠ197638 to honour Yahweh's nameÂŠ197639, and bring God's sacredÂŠ197635 items\add*.â
\c 23
\rem /s1 Families of the Levites and Their Functions; Duties of the Levites; The Levites
\p
\v 1 \add âBy then DavidÂŠ197644 was old and coming to the end of his life\add*, and heÂŠ197645 made his son Shelomoh \add (SolomonÂŠ197651)\add* kingÂŠ197648 over YisraelÂŠ197655.\x + \xo 23:1: \xt 1Ki 1:1-40.\x*
\s1 The Levite families and their assignments
\rem /s1 The Work of the Levites
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 2 ThenÂŠ197657 \add @David\add* gathered all the IsraeliÂŠ197663 officials and the priestsÂŠ197664 and LevitesÂŠ197665.
\v 3 Counting the LeviteÂŠ197668 males that were thirty years old andÂŠ197667 older, they found there were thirty-eight thousandÂŠ197679 menÂŠ197676.
\v 4 \add David assigned\add* twenty-four thousand of them to supervise the workÂŠ197685 at Yahweh's temple, sixÂŠ197694 thousand to be officialsÂŠ197692 and judgesÂŠ197693,
\v 5 four thousand to be gatekeepersÂŠ197699, andÂŠ197697 four thousand to praiseÂŠ197707 YahwehÂŠ197703 using the musical instrumentsÂŠ197704 thatÂŠ197705 he'd provided.
\p
\v 6 \add âSoÂŠ197709\add* DavidÂŠ197710 dividedÂŠ197709 \add @the Levites\add* into divisionsÂŠ197711 accordingÂŠ197713 to \add their ancestry through\add* Levi'sÂŠ197714 sonsÂŠ197713 GershonÂŠ197715, KohatÂŠ197716, andÂŠ197717 MerariÂŠ197717.
\s1 The Gershonites
\rem /s1 The Gershonites; Gershonites
\p
\v 7 The Gershonites \add included\add* LadanÂŠ197721 andÂŠ197722 ShimeiÂŠ197722.
\v 8 Ladan'sÂŠ197726 threeÂŠ197731 sonsÂŠ197725 were: YehielÂŠ197728 (the oldest), ZetamÂŠ197729, and YoelÂŠ197730.
\v 9 Shimei'sÂŠ197735\f + \fr 23:9 \ft Possibly the wrong name got into the Hebrew here, because it disagrees with v10.\f* threeÂŠ197740 sonsÂŠ197734 were: Shelomot, HazielÂŠ197738, and HaranÂŠ197739. (They were leaders of Ladan'sÂŠ197744 clans.)
\v 10 Shimei'sÂŠ197748 four sons were: Yahat, ZinaÂŠ197750,\f + \fr 23:10 \ft Some ancient translations have Zizah here, which would seem to fit better with v11.\f* YeushÂŠ197751, and BeriahÂŠ197752.
\v 11 (YahatÂŠ197761 was the head, and ZizahÂŠ197763 was secondÂŠ197764. YeushÂŠ197765 and BeriahÂŠ197766 were \add âgrouped together as one family unit as they only had few descendants\add*.)
\s2 The Kohatites
\rem /s1 Kohathites; The Kohathites
\p
\v 12 Kohat'sÂŠ197779 fourÂŠ197784 sonsÂŠ197778 were: AmramÂŠ197780, Yitshar, Hevron, andÂŠ197783 UzzielÂŠ197783.
\v 13 Amram'sÂŠ197788 sons were Aharon and MoshehÂŠ197790 \add (AaronÂŠ197789 and MosesÂŠ197790)\add*. Aharon \add âand his future male descendants were permanently appointed\add* to consecrateÂŠ197793 the most sacredÂŠ197794 things, to burn incenseÂŠ197802, to ministerÂŠ197805 to YahwehÂŠ197804, and to blessÂŠ197806 his nameÂŠ197807.\x + \xo 23:13: \xt Exo 28:1.\x*
\v 14 MoshehÂŠ197812 \add was known as\add* \add âa manÂŠ197813 who served\add* God, andÂŠ197812 his descendants were included with the \add other\add* Levites.
\v 15 Mosheh'sÂŠ197823 sonsÂŠ197822 were GershomÂŠ197824 andÂŠ197825 EliezerÂŠ197825.
\v 16 Gershom'sÂŠ197828 eldest son was ShevuelÂŠ197829.
\v 17 Eliezer'sÂŠ197835 only son was Rehavyah, but Rehavyah \add went on to\add* have many sons.
\p
\v 18 Yitshar'sÂŠ197850 eldest son was ShelomotÂŠ197851.
\v 19 Hevron's sonsÂŠ197855 \add âfrom oldest to youngest\add* were: Yeriyyah, AmaryahÂŠ197859, YahazielÂŠ197861, andÂŠ197863 Yekamean.
\v 20 Uzziel'sÂŠ197867 sonsÂŠ197866 were MikahÂŠ197868 andÂŠ197870 YishshiyahÂŠ197870.
\s2 The Merarites
\rem /s1 The Merarites; Merarites
\p
\v 21 Merari'sÂŠ197875 sons were Mahli and MushiÂŠ197877, \add and\add* Mahli sons were EleazarÂŠ197880 and KishÂŠ197881.
\v 22 EleazarÂŠ197884 died without having any sons, \add so\add* his brother Kish'sÂŠ197897 sons marriedÂŠ197894 his daughtersÂŠ197893 \add (to continue the family name)\add*.
\v 23 MushiÂŠ197901 had threeÂŠ197905 sonsÂŠ197900: MahliÂŠ197902, EderÂŠ197903, and YerimotÂŠ197904.
\p
\v 24 Those were Levi'sÂŠ197910 descendantsÂŠ197908 \add âby their clans and their appointments, who did the workÂŠ197921 of servingÂŠ197921 in Yahweh's temple once theyÂŠ197915 reached twentyÂŠ197925 years old\add*,
\v 25 because DavidÂŠ197931 had saidÂŠ197930, âYisrael'sÂŠ197936 godÂŠ197934 YahwehÂŠ197933 has givenÂŠ197932 peace to his peopleÂŠ197937, andÂŠ197938 he'll \add now\add* live foreverÂŠ197942 in YerushalemÂŠ197939,
\v 26 so the LevitesÂŠ197945 won'tÂŠ197946 need to carryÂŠ197948 the \add sacredÂŠ197951\add* tentÂŠ197951 anymore, along with all its equipment.â\x + \xo 23:26: \xt Deu 10:8.\x*
\v 27 \add âSo one of David'sÂŠ197961 final instructions had been to count the Levite men who were twentyÂŠ197969 years old andÂŠ197971 over\add*,
\v 28 because their work was to \add âassistÂŠ197975\add* Aharon's descendantsÂŠ197977 in their work in Yahweh's temple. They \add âwere in charge\add* of the temple courtyardsÂŠ197984 and siderooms, \add âin charge of the purificationÂŠ197990 ceremonies\add*, and did other work at the temple.\x + \xo 23:28-32: \xt Num 3:5-9.\x*
\v 29 \add âĄThey were also in charge of\add* the sacred bread, as well as the fine flourÂŠ198001 for the offering, the wafersÂŠ198003 of bread without rising agent, the baking pans, and \add âall the measuringÂŠ198009 and mixing of ingredients\add*.
\p
\v 30 Every morning and every eveningÂŠ198019 \add @the Levites\add* stood and praisedÂŠ198016 YahwehÂŠ198017.
\v 31 They would also do that on the rest days, and at the new moon celebrations and during the other religious festivalsÂŠ198027. \add âThere were regulations about how many of them must always be on duty serving\add* YahwehÂŠ198024.
\v 32 They were \add also\add* in charge of the sacredÂŠ198044 tent and the holy placeÂŠ198044 and assisting \add the priests\add* (their relatives, Aharon's descendantsÂŠ198046) in their serviceÂŠ198049 at Yahweh's temple.
\c 24
\s1 The Levites' duties
\rem /s1 The Work Assigned to the Priests; Duties of the Priests; Divisions of the Priests; The Divisions of Priests
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 Aharon's sons were: Nadav, Avihu, EleazarÂŠ198061, and ItamarÂŠ198062,
\v 2 \add âbut\add* Nadav and Avihu diedÂŠ198064 \add âbefore theirÂŠ198068 fatherÂŠ198068\add* and \add âwithout having any children, so\add* \add only\add* EleazarÂŠ198075 and ItamarÂŠ198076 became priestsÂŠ198074.\x + \xo 24:2: \xt Lev 10:1-2.\x*
\v 3 DavidÂŠ198079 \add âgave Eleazar'sÂŠ198084 descendant TsadokÂŠ198080, andÂŠ198078 Itamar'sÂŠ198089 descendant AhimelekÂŠ198085 two different sets of dutiesÂŠ198090 to perform\add*.
\v 4 \add âThere were more leaders among Eleazar's descendants than there were among Itamar's descendants, so they appointed sixteen leaders from Eleazar's descendants andÂŠ198093 eightÂŠ198117 from Itamar's descendants\add*.
\v 5 They dividedÂŠ198119 up \add âthe duties by lots so some of the leaders from each of the two groups served the facility andÂŠ198119 others served God directly\add*. DOUBLE-CHECK, along with v3.
\v 6 Netanel'sÂŠ198143 son ShemayahÂŠ198140 was the LeviteÂŠ198147 scribeÂŠ198144 who recordedÂŠ198139 all this in frontÂŠ198148 of the kingÂŠ198149 and the leaders, TsadokÂŠ198151 the priest and Abiatar'sÂŠ198156 son Ahimelek, and the clan leaders of the priestsÂŠ198159 and the LevitesÂŠ198147. (One familyÂŠ198158 was drawn by lot from Eleazar'sÂŠ198166 group, and then the next from Itamar'sÂŠ198170, etc.)
\p
\v 7 The firstÂŠ198175 two \add âallocations of duties\add* wentÂŠ198173 to Yehoyariv andÂŠ198173 then YedayahÂŠ198177.
\v 8 Next were Harim and SeorimÂŠ198182,
\v 9 Malkiyyah and Miyyamin,
\v 10 Hakkots and Aviyyah,
\v 11 Yeshua and Shekanyah,
\v 12 Elyashiv and YakimÂŠ198203,
\v 13 Huppah and Yesheveav,
\v 14 BilgahÂŠ198214 and ImmerÂŠ198217,
\v 15 Hezer and Ha-Pitstsets,
\v 16 Patahyah and Yehezkel,
\v 17 Yakin and GamulÂŠ198237,
\v 18 Delayah and lastly, MaazyahÂŠ198244.
\p
\v 19 Those \add were the priests\add* selected to \add be leaders of the groups\add* that would serve in Yahweh's temple, following the instructions that Yisrael's godÂŠ198263 Yahweh had given theirÂŠ198256 ancestor Aharon.
