\p
\v 1 Then DavidÂŠ198382 and the army chiefs allocated the \add musical\add* service to the sons of AsafÂŠ198387, Heyman, and Yedutunâthe ones prophesyingÂŠ198390 with harpsÂŠ198394, with lyresÂŠ198393, and with cymbalsÂŠ198395. \add âThis is a list of the menÂŠ198398 whom they chose for that workÂŠ198385\add*:
\li1
\v 2 From Asaf'sÂŠ198403 sons: Zakkur, YosefÂŠ198405, Netanyah, and AsarelahÂŠ198407. They were supervised by Asaf, who prophesiedÂŠ198414 \add âunder the king's direction\add*.
\li1
\v 3 Six from Yedutun's family: GedalyahÂŠ198423, TseriÂŠ198424, YeshayahÂŠ198425, Hashavyah, and MattityahÂŠ198427. They were supervised by Yedutun, who prophesiedÂŠ198434 with a harp, and thankedÂŠ198437 and praisedÂŠ198438 YahwehÂŠ198439.
\li1
\v 4 From Heman'sÂŠ198442 sonsÂŠ198443: Bukkiyah, MattanyahÂŠ198446, UzzielÂŠ198447, Shuvael, Yerimot, HananyahÂŠ198450, HananiÂŠ198451, EliatahÂŠ198452, GiddaltiÂŠ198453, Romamti-Ezer, YoshbekashahÂŠ198456, MallotiÂŠ198457, HotirÂŠ198458, and MahaziotÂŠ198459.
\v 5 They were all sons of King David's prophet HemanÂŠ198465 \add âwho'd been promisedÂŠ198468 by God that he'd strengthen him\add*, and God gave him fourteen sons and threeÂŠ198479 daughtersÂŠ198478.
\p
\v 6 All of those served as musiciansÂŠ198488 in Yahweh's temple under theirÂŠ198487 fathers' supervisionâthey played cymbalsÂŠ198491, harps, and lyres. \add âTheir fathers were supervised by\add* the kingÂŠ198499.
\v 7 There were 288 of those men andÂŠ198519 theirÂŠ198509 musical relativesÂŠ198509 who played to YahwehÂŠ198513.
\v 8 They used lots to determine their duties, whether young or old, andÂŠ198521 \add âirrespective of their musical abilities\add*.
\p
\v 9 The firstÂŠ198535 allocation wentÂŠ198533 (in order) to:
\li1 AsafÂŠ198536 and his son YosefÂŠ198537,
\li1 GedalyahÂŠ198538 and his relativesÂŠ198542 and sonsÂŠ198543 (a total of twelve),
