\v 31 Romamti-Ezer and his sonsÂŠ198711 and relativesÂŠ198712 (twelve).
\c 26
\s1 The guards of doorway of temple
\rem /s1 The Gatekeepers; Duties of the Gatekeepers; The Temple Guards
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 These were the divisionÂŠ198717 of the gatekeepersÂŠ198718:
\li1 From the Korahites: Kore'sÂŠ198723 son MeshelemyahÂŠ198720 (Kore was one of Asaf'sÂŠ198727 sonsÂŠ198726),
\li1
\v 2 Meshelemyah's \add seven\add* sonsÂŠ198730 (in order): Zekaryah, YediaelÂŠ198733, ZebadyahÂŠ198735, Yatniel,
\v 3 Eylam, YehohananÂŠ198742, and Elyehoenai.
\li1
\v 4 Oved-Edom's \add eight\add* sonsÂŠ198749 (in order): ShemayahÂŠ198750, Yehozavad, YoahÂŠ198754, SakarÂŠ198756, NetanelÂŠ198758,\x + \xo 26:4-5: \xt 2Sam 6:11; 1Ch 13:14.\x*
\v 5 Ammiel, Yissakar, and PeulletaiÂŠ198765. (GodÂŠ198769 had blessedÂŠ198768 himÂŠ198768.)
\li1
\v 6 Oved-Edom's son ShemayahÂŠ198772 also had sonsÂŠ198775. (They were leaders in theirÂŠ198778 father's family because theyÂŠ198783 were capable warriors.)
\v 7 Shemayah'sÂŠ198786 sons were: OtniÂŠ198787, RefaelÂŠ198788, Oved, and Elzavad. His relatives ElihuÂŠ198795 and Semakyah were also capable men.
\p
\v 8 All those descendants of Oved-EdomÂŠ198804 and their sons and relativesÂŠ198807 were capable people and strong workers. Altogether there were 62 of them.
\li1
\v 9 Meshelemyah had sons andÂŠ198818 relativesÂŠ198820 who were respected (eighteenÂŠ198824 in total).
\li1
\v 10 Merari'sÂŠ198833 descendantÂŠ198831 Hosah'sÂŠ198828 sonsÂŠ198834: ShimriÂŠ198835 (not actually the firstborn, but his fatherÂŠ198843 appointed himÂŠ198842 as the first),
\v 11 Hilkiyah, Tavalyah, and Zekaryah. (Thirteen total sonsÂŠ198854 and relativesÂŠ198855.)
\p
\v 12 Those men were leaders of the groups of men who guarded the gates of the temple. They worked in Yahweh's temple like theirÂŠ198867 relativesÂŠ198867 did.
\v 13 \add âThey used lots to assign each family to a particular gate, irrespective of the family reputation\add*.
\v 14 Shelemyah'sÂŠ198885 group was allocated to the easternÂŠ198884 gate, and his son ZekaryahÂŠ198886 (a wise adviser) was allocated to the northernÂŠ198895 gate.
\v 15 Oved-Edom's group was allocated to the southernÂŠ198900 gate, plus his sonsÂŠ198901 \add were to guard\add* the storehousesÂŠ198903.
\v 16 Shuppim'sÂŠ198905 and Hosah'sÂŠ198906 groups were allocated the western gate, along with the ShalleketÂŠ198910 gate on the uphill road with \add âside-by-side guards\add*.
\v 17 Every day there were six LevitesÂŠ198918 on duty in the east, four in the northÂŠ198920, four in the southÂŠ198923, and two at the storehousesÂŠ198926.
\v 18 There were fourÂŠ198932 on the roadÂŠ198933 by the western courtyard, and twoÂŠ198934 in the courtyard.
\v 19 Those were the groups of men who were Korah's andÂŠ198942 Merari'sÂŠ198943 descendantsÂŠ198940 who guarded the temple gates.
\s1 The guards of things/objects
\rem /s1 Other Temple Duties; The Treasurers and Other Officials; Treasurers and Other Officials; The Treasurers, Officers, and Judges
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 20 The Levite, Ahiyyah was \add âin charge of\add* the temple treasuriesÂŠ198952, as well as the storehousesÂŠ198949 for dedicatedÂŠ198953 giftsÂŠ198953.
\v 21 Ladam's descendants (\add also\add* descendants of Gershon) \add âwere leaders among their familyÂŠ198961 groups. Yehiel was a descendant of this LadanÂŠ198956\add*.
\v 22 Yehiel's sonsÂŠ198966 were ZetamÂŠ198968 and YoelÂŠ198969, \add and they\add* \add âwere in charge of\add* the storehousesÂŠ198973 in Yahweh's temple.
\p
\v 23 \add Others who did that work\add* \add âwere descendants of Amram, Yitshar, Hevron and Uzziel\add*.
\p
\v 24 Shuvael, a descendant of Mosheh'sÂŠ198988 son GershomÂŠ198985, was \add another\add* leader in charge of the treasuriesÂŠ198992,
\v 25 along with his relativesÂŠ198994: Eliezer'sÂŠ198995 son Rehavyah, Rehavyah's son Yeshayah, Yeshayah'sÂŠ198998 son Yoram, Yoram'sÂŠ199000 son Zikri, andÂŠ198994 Zikri'sÂŠ199002 son ShelomotÂŠ199004.
\v 26 ShelomotÂŠ199009 and his relativesÂŠ199010 \add âsupervised\add* all the storehousesÂŠ199014 for the sacred things thatÂŠ199016 were consecratedÂŠ199017 by King DavidÂŠ199018, the \add âclan leaders\add*, and the army division leaders and other commanders
\v 27 who had dedicated some of the plunder \add âfrom their battlesÂŠ199031\add* to the repairÂŠ199036 of Yahweh'sÂŠ199038 residence.
\v 28 Shelomot and his relativesÂŠ199062 were also in charge of everythingÂŠ199056 that the prophet Shemuel, \add King\add* ShaulÂŠ199044 (Kish'sÂŠ199047 son), and David's two army commanders AbnerÂŠ199048 (Ner'sÂŠ199051 son) and Yoav (Tseruyah's son) had dedicated \add to Yahweh\add*.
\s1 Other Levites' duties
\rem /s1 Duties of Other Levites
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 29 From Yitshar's descendants, KenanyahÂŠ199066 and his sonsÂŠ199067 worked outsideÂŠ199069 \add the temple area\add* as officialsÂŠ199073 and judgesÂŠ199074 over YisraelÂŠ199072.
\p
\v 30 From Hevron's descendants, Hashavyah and his relativesÂŠ199078 were responsible for all the work done for YahwehÂŠ199094 and for the kingÂŠ199096 in the area west of the YordanÂŠ199090 river. There were 1,700 of them \add âwho were able to do their work well\add*.
\v 31 According to the records of Hevron's descendants, Yeriyyah was theirÂŠ199102 leader. (In the fortiethÂŠ199105 yearÂŠ199104 of David'sÂŠ199107 reignÂŠ199106, theyÂŠ199108 had searched \add ?in those records\add* andÂŠ199109 discovered that there were powerful men in YazerÂŠ199113 in GileadÂŠ199114.)
\v 32 \add @Yeriyyah\add* had 2,700 relativesÂŠ199116 who were strong \add workers\add* and \add âleaders of their familiesÂŠ199124\add*. King DavidÂŠ199126 \add âput them in charge of governing\add* the tribes of Reuven, Gad, and the eastern half of the tribe of Menashsheh, \add âto ensure that all the people did what God commanded and what the king told them to do\add*.
\c 27
\s1 King David's officials
\rem /s1 The Military Divisions; Army Divisions; Military and Civil Organization; Military Commanders and Divisions
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 This is a list of the IsraeliÂŠ199144 men who served the kingÂŠ199157 \add in the army\add*. Some were leaders of familiesÂŠ199148, some were commanders of divisions of one thousand, some were commanders of division of one hundredÂŠ199152, and some were other officersÂŠ199153. There were twenty-four thousand men in each group, and each group served one monthÂŠ199167 each yearÂŠ199168.
\li1
\v 2 Zavdiel's son Yashoveam, was in charge of the group that served during the first monthÂŠ199179 each year.
\rem /s1 Administration of the Tribes of Israel
\v 3 \add He\add* was a descendantÂŠ199193 of Perets and was the commanderÂŠ199199 of all the \add âarmy officers\add* during the firstÂŠ199202 monthÂŠ199201 \add each year\add*.
\li1
\v 4 DodaiÂŠ199209 (the AhohitesÂŠ199210) was the commander of the group that served during the secondÂŠ199208 monthÂŠ199207 each year. MiklotÂŠ199212 was \add also\add* a leader in that group.
\li1
\v 5 BenayahÂŠ199226, son of YehoyadaÂŠ199229 the high priestÂŠ199230, was the commanderÂŠ199221 of the group that served during the third monthÂŠ199224 each year.
\v 6 \add *He\add* was the strongest of âthe thirtyâ and was their leader. His son was Ammizavad.
\li1
\v 7 The fourth \add leader\add* for the fourth monthÂŠ199251 was Yoav's brotherÂŠ199256 Asahel, and then his son Zevadyah succeeded himÂŠ199260. His divisionÂŠ199262 was twenty-four thousandÂŠ199265 \add men\add*.
\li1
\v 8 The fifth \add leader\add* for the fifth monthÂŠ199269 was the commanderÂŠ199271 ShamhutÂŠ199272 the Yizrahite. His divisionÂŠ199275 was twenty-four thousandÂŠ199278 \add men\add*.
\li1
\v 9 The sixth \add leader\add* for the sixth monthÂŠ199282 was Ikkesh'sÂŠ199287 son IraÂŠ199284 the TekoiteÂŠ199288. His divisionÂŠ199290 was twenty-four thousandÂŠ199293 \add men\add*.
\li1
\v 10 The seventh \add leader\add* for the seventh monthÂŠ199297 was Helets the Peloite (an Eframite). His divisionÂŠ199306 was twenty-four thousandÂŠ199309 \add men\add*.
\li1
\v 11 The eighth \add leader\add* for the eighth monthÂŠ199313 was Sivkay the HushatiteÂŠ199316 (a Zerahite). His divisionÂŠ199319 was twenty-four thousandÂŠ199322 \add men\add*.
\li1
