\c 28
\s1 David's temple plans
\rem /s1 Solomon Instructed to Build the Temple; David's Instructions for the Temple; David's Plans for the Temple; David's Instructions to Solomon
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add âNow\add* DavidÂŠ199668 called all Yisrael's leaders to assembleÂŠ199667 in YerushalemÂŠ199706: the tribal leaders, the leaders of the \add various\add* divisionsÂŠ199678 that servedÂŠ199679 the king, the commanders of army units of thousandsÂŠ199684 and of hundredsÂŠ199686, and the supervisors of all the propertyÂŠ199690 and cattle belonging to the king and his sons, along with the tops officials, and the warriors including \add âtheir powerful heroes\add*.
\p
\v 2 ThenÂŠ199708 King DavidÂŠ199709 stood up and spoke, âListen to me, my brothersÂŠ199716 and my peopleÂŠ199717, I had in my heartÂŠ199721 to put up a building for the box containing Yahweh's covenantÂŠ199726 to rest in. It's the footstoolÂŠ199729 of our god's feet of our god and I've made preparationsÂŠ199732 to start building,\x + \xo 28:2-7: \xt 2Sam 7:1-16; 1Ch 17:1-14.\x*
\v 3 but GodÂŠ199735 told me that I wouldn't be the one to buildÂŠ199740 a houseÂŠ199741 to \add âhonour him\add* because I've \add âbeen involved in a lot of war andÂŠ199747 killings\add*.
\p
\v 4 âYet Yisrael's godÂŠ199752 YahwehÂŠ199751 chose me from all of my father's family to be king over Yisrael foreverÂŠ199764, because he chose a leaderÂŠ199768 from \add the tribe of\add* YehudahÂŠ199766, my father' tribe, andÂŠ199750 among the sons of my father, with me he was pleasedÂŠ199776 to make king over all IsraelÂŠ199753.
\v 5 ThenÂŠ199784 out of the many sons that he's givenÂŠ199790 me, he choseÂŠ199793 my son Shelomoh \add (SolomonÂŠ199794)\add* to \add âbe the next king to rule his kingdomÂŠ199800 of\add* YisraelÂŠ199804.
\p
\v 6 âThenÂŠ199806 he told me, âYour son Shelomoh is the one who will buildÂŠ199812 my temple and the courtyardsÂŠ199814 \add around it\add*, because I've chosenÂŠ199817 him to be like my son and I'll be like a fatherÂŠ199825 to him.
\v 7 I'll establishÂŠ199827 his kingdomÂŠ199830 foreverÂŠ199833, if he's diligent at following my instructions andÂŠ199827 \add obeying\add* my judgements, like he is at present.â
\p
\v 8 â\add âSoÂŠ199843\add* now, in \add âfront\add* of all YisraelÂŠ199847, Yahweh's assemblyÂŠ199848, and in the ears of our god, \add I challenge you all to discover and obey\add* all the commandsÂŠ199857 of your god Yahweh so that you'll all possessÂŠ199861 the goodÂŠ199865 land and you'll all leaveÂŠ199866 your sons afterÂŠ199868 you to inheritÂŠ199866 it forever.
\p
\v 9 âAnd you, Shelomoh my son, \add âfollow\add* your father's godÂŠ199881 and serveÂŠ199883 him with a whole heartÂŠ199884 and with a willingÂŠ199887 life, because YahwehÂŠ199893 \add âlooks into\add* all heartsÂŠ199891, and understandsÂŠ199898 all \add âyour motives\add*. If you look for him, he'll \add make sure\add* you find him, but if you abandonÂŠ199906 him, he'll rejectÂŠ199907 you forever.
\v 10 You can now see that you need to be strongÂŠ199922 and get busy, because YahwehÂŠ199915 has chosenÂŠ199916 you to erect a buildingÂŠ199918 to be his sanctuaryÂŠ199921.â
\p
\v 11 Then DavidÂŠ199927 gave the plans for \add the temple\add* to his son Shelomoh, \add including plans\add* for its porch, its houses, its treasuriesÂŠ199937, its upperÂŠ199938 rooms and its innerÂŠ199940 rooms, and the \add âroom to contain the sacred box\add*.
\v 12 \add He also handed over\add* the plans he envisioned for the temple courtyardsÂŠ199950, all the surrounding apartments, all the treasuries, andÂŠ199944 all the storerooms for sacred things.
\v 13 \add He included instructions\add* for the divisionsÂŠ199964 of the priestsÂŠ199965 and LevitesÂŠ199966, for all the \add âservices required to operate the temple, and for all the equipment and utensils needed for all that\add*.
\v 14 \add David had determined\add* the weight of goldÂŠ199984 and silverÂŠ199992 would be needed to make all the necessary items that would be used in the regular temple functions,
\v 15 \add including\add* the gold lampstands and lamps and the silverÂŠ200011 lampstands and lamps,
\v 16 and the goldÂŠ200021 for the display tables, and the silver for the silver tables.
\v 17 \add âAlso\add* the pure gold meat forksÂŠ200031 and the jugs and basinsÂŠ200032, and the weights of the gold and silverÂŠ200042 bowls.
\v 18 ThenÂŠ200047 the weightÂŠ200051 of refinedÂŠ200050 gold for the incenseÂŠ200048 altarÂŠ200047, andÂŠ200047 for making the winged creatures that spreadÂŠ200056 out across the top of the box \add âcontaining\add* Yahweh'sÂŠ200063 agreement,
\v 19 \add saying\add*, âI've written down all those plans \add âwith Yahweh's direction as he gave me instructions for what has to be done\add*.â
\v 20 Then DavidÂŠ200077 told his son Shelomoh, âBe strongÂŠ200080 and courageousÂŠ200081, and \add âget going\add*. Don't be afraidÂŠ200085 or discouraged because Yahweh GodÂŠ200091, my god, is with you. He won't leave you and he won't abandonÂŠ200097 you untilÂŠ200098 all the workÂŠ200104 of \add âconstructing\add* Yahweh's residence \add âand the necessary equipment\add* is finishedÂŠ200100.
\v 21 Listen, the divisionsÂŠ200110 of the priestsÂŠ200111 and the LevitesÂŠ200112 for all the service of the god's houseÂŠ200116 and all the \add âskilledÂŠ200125 workmen will be backing you in all the workÂŠ200115\add*. The officialsÂŠ200129 and all the peopleÂŠ200132 are \add âready to follow your instructions\add*.â
\c 29
\s1 Donations for the temple
\rem /s1 Gifts for Building the Temple; Solomon succeeds David as king; Offerings for Building the Temple
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 Then King DavidÂŠ200139 told the entire assemblyÂŠ200143, âMy son Shelomoh \add (SolomonÂŠ200144)\add* \add âhas been chosenÂŠ200147 by God himself\add*. He's young and tender, and \add âit's a hugeÂŠ200154 job\add* because the templeÂŠ200158 isn'tÂŠ200156 being built for people, but for YahwehÂŠ200160 God.\x + \xo 29:1-2: \xt 1Ch 22:5.\x*
\v 2 \add âI'veÂŠ200166 used all my resources to provide a plentiful supply of materials\add* for my god's residence: the gold for the gold things, and the silver for the silver things, the bronze for the bronze things, the iron for the iron things, the wood for the wooden parts, onyx stones for inlays, antimonyÂŠ200187 stones and colourfulÂŠ200188 things, and all the rare stones and alabasterÂŠ200194 stones.
\v 3 What's more, because I'm excited to have my god's residence \add built\add*, I've donated my own personal goldÂŠ200205 andÂŠ200206 silverÂŠ200206 on top of everything else that I've preparedÂŠ200214 for the sacredÂŠ200216 temple:
\v 4 100 tonnes of gold and 2,500 tonnes of refinedÂŠ200229 silverÂŠ200228 for overlayingÂŠ200230 the buildings' wallsÂŠ200231,
\v 5 \add as well as\add* gold for the gold things, silver for the silver things, and for everything \add âto be made\add* by the craftsmenÂŠ200242. \add âSo\add* who is willing today, \add âto commit themselves\add* to makingÂŠ200244 a contributionÂŠ200244 towards Yahweh's work?
\p
\v 6 ThenÂŠ200256 the familyÂŠ200252 leaders and the leaders of the \add âtribesÂŠ200255\add*, and the \add âvarious levels of military\add* commandersÂŠ200257, and the king'sÂŠ200262 \add âconstruction overseers\add*, \add all\add* contributed willinglyÂŠ200250.
\v 7 TheyÂŠ200268 donated \add a total of\add* 170 tonnes of gold and 100kg of gold coins, 350 tonnes of silverÂŠ200276, 600 tonnes of bronzeÂŠ200280, and 3,400 tonnes of iron for the \add âtemple\add* construction,
\v 8 plus anyone who had precious stonesÂŠ200293 donated them to the treasuryÂŠ200295 for the \add âtemple\add*. Yehiel (a Gershonite) \add âwas in charge of those\add*.
\v 9 The peopleÂŠ200306 were \add âexcited\add*, becauseÂŠ200307 they'dÂŠ200313 \add all\add* givenÂŠ200309 willinglyÂŠ200309 to YahwehÂŠ200314, andÂŠ200315 King DavidÂŠ200316 was also very pleased.
\s1 The praying for David
\rem /s1 David's Prayer of Praise; David's Praise to God; David Praises God; David's Prayer
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 10 Then \add King\add* DavidÂŠ200324 blessed Yahweh in \add âfront of\add* the entireÂŠ200329 assemblyÂŠ200331, saying, âBlessed are youÂŠ200335, Yahweh, GodÂŠ200337 of YisraelÂŠ200338, ourÂŠ200339 fatherÂŠ200339, from the ages past and until the ages to come.
\v 11 Greatness and the powerÂŠ200348, beauty and splendour and majestyÂŠ200351 \add all belong\add* to you, Yahweh, as indeed does everythingÂŠ200354 in the heavensÂŠ200355 and on the earthÂŠ200356. The kingdomÂŠ200359 and \add âsupreme leadership\add* \add all belongs\add* to you, Yahweh.\x + \xo 29:11: \xt Mat 6:13.\x*
\v 12 Wealth and \add prestige comes from you\add*, and you rule over everything. \add âYou have the powerÂŠ200372 and strength and control\add* to make \add people\add* greatÂŠ200375 and to strengthen everyone,
\v 13 \add âso\add* now, our godÂŠ200380, we're thankingÂŠ200381 you andÂŠ200379 praisingÂŠ200384 yourÂŠ200386 beautiful nameÂŠ200385.
\p
\v 14 ButÂŠ200388 who am I, and who are my peopleÂŠ200392, that we should \add âbe in a position to be able\add* to donate freely like this? \add âYes,\add* everythingÂŠ200402 comes from you, and \add âwe've simply givenÂŠ200404 back from what you gaveÂŠ200404 to us\add*,
\v 15 because we're \add just\add* strangers on the earth \add âin yourÂŠ200411 eyes\add*, and foreign guests like all our ancestorsÂŠ200415. Our time on the earth is like a shadowÂŠ200416 \add âwithout any permanence\add*.
\v 16 YahwehÂŠ200425 our godÂŠ200426, all this abundanceÂŠ200428 thatÂŠ200430 we have \add âcollected\add* in order to buildÂŠ200432 a houseÂŠ200435 for you, for your holy nameÂŠ200436, \add âoriginally it came from you and it all belongs to you\add* \add anyway\add*.
\v 17 \add âYes\add* I knowÂŠ200444, my godÂŠ200445, that you examine our hearts and you'reÂŠ200447 pleasedÂŠ200451 \add âwhen we do what is right\add*. I have freely offered all theseÂŠ200458 \add gifts\add* \add âas I strive to do what is right\add*, and now \add âI'm also happy to\add* see your peopleÂŠ200460 to freely offer \add gifts\add* to you.
\v 18 YahwehÂŠ200470, the godÂŠ200471 of our ancestorsÂŠ200475 AbrahamÂŠ200472, Yitshak \add (IsaacÂŠ200473)\add*, and YisraelÂŠ200474 \add (IsraelÂŠ200474)\add*, \add help yourÂŠ200483 peopleÂŠ200483 continue to desire to do things like this foreverÂŠ200479, and help them remain loyal to youÂŠ200486\add*.
\v 19 \add âAlso,\add* giveÂŠ200490 my son Shelomoh \add (Solomon)\add* a \add âsincere desire\add* to follow your instructions, your testimonies, and your regulationsÂŠ200496, and to do \add âeverything needed\add* to buildÂŠ200499 the templeÂŠ200500 \add âfollowing all my preparationÂŠ200503 work\add*.â
\p
\v 20 Then DavidÂŠ200507 told all the assembled \add people\add*, âBless yourÂŠ200517 godÂŠ200517 Yahweh.â and the entireÂŠ200519 assembly blessedÂŠ200511 Yahweh, the god of theirÂŠ200524 ancestorsÂŠ200524. Then they bowedÂŠ200525 down to \add âhonour\add* \add both\add* Yahweh and the kingÂŠ200528.
\rem /s1 Solomon Named as King; Solomon Acknowledged as King
\p
\v 21 ThenÂŠ200530 they offered sacrifices to Yahweh, and sacrificed burntÂŠ200535 offerings to Yahweh on the following day: 1,000 bullsÂŠ200540, 1,000 rams, 1,000 lambsÂŠ200544, plus theirÂŠ200546 drinkÂŠ200546 offerings and sacrifices for all YisraelÂŠ200551 in abundance.
\v 22 They ateÂŠ200553 and drankÂŠ200554 \add âin Yahweh's honour\add* that dayÂŠ200557 with greatÂŠ200560 celebration.
\rem /s1 Solomon Anointed King
\p ThenÂŠ200553 they rededicated David'sÂŠ200566 son Shelomoh \add (SolomonÂŠ200563)\add* as kingÂŠ200561, and anointedÂŠ200567 him as leader \add âon Yahweh's behalf\add* and TsadokÂŠ200570 as priestÂŠ200571.
\v 23 Shelomoh satÂŠ200573 on Yahweh's throneÂŠ200577 as kingÂŠ200580 \add âreplacing\add* his fatherÂŠ200584 DavidÂŠ200583, and he prosperedÂŠ200585 and all YisraelÂŠ200590 listened to him.\x + \xo 29:23: \xt 1Ki 2:12.\x*
\v 24 All the leadersÂŠ200594 andÂŠ200592 the mightyÂŠ200595 warriors, as well as all the sonsÂŠ200599 of King DavidÂŠ200601, \add âpledged allegiance to\add* King Shelomoh.
\v 25 YahwehÂŠ200609 made Shelomoh exceedingly great in the eyes of all Yisrael, andÂŠ200618 bestowed a kingdom on himÂŠ200631, the majestyÂŠ200620 of whichÂŠ200622 hadn't previously been on any kingÂŠ200630 over Yisrael.
\s1 The story of David's kingdom
