\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 26 Yesse'sÂŠ200640 \add (Jesse's)\add* son DavidÂŠ200637 was the king who ruled all YisraelÂŠ200646 \add (IsraelÂŠ200646)\add*
\v 27 and he ruled for fortyÂŠ200654 years: from Hevron city for sevenÂŠ200658 years, and thenÂŠ200648 thirty-three years from YerushalemÂŠ200660.\x + \xo 29:27: \xt 2Sam 5:4-5; 1Ch 3:4.\x*
\v 28 He \add âlived a long life with\add* riches and splendour, and diedÂŠ200665 at a goodÂŠ200667 old age. ThenÂŠ200665 his son Shelomoh \add (SolomonÂŠ200673)\add* \add âreplaced him as king\add*.
\v 29 \add The records\add* of \add âeverything done by\add* King DavidÂŠ200678, \add âfrom the beginning to his end\add*, were writtenÂŠ200683 by the prophetsÂŠ200693 Shemuel \add (SamuelÂŠ200687)\add*, NatanÂŠ200692 \add (NathanÂŠ200692)\add*, andÂŠ200677 GadÂŠ200697.
\v 30 They \add âwrote\add* about his powerfulÂŠ200704 rule, and all the things thatÂŠ200706 happened to him and to the Israeli people, and in the kingdomsÂŠ200715 of \add âother countries while he was ruling YisraelÂŠ200711\add*.
